'''Shen Yiqin''' ({{zh|c=谌贻琴|p=Shèn Yìqín}}; born December 1959) is a Chinese politician of [[Bai people|Bai]] ethnic heritage serving since September 2017 as the [[Politics of Guizhou|Governor]] of [[Guizhou]], a province in southwestern China.  She is the first female Governor of Guizhou in history.

==Career==
Shen was born in [[Zhijin County]], Guizhou. Shen belonged to a group of [[sent-down youth]] in the latter years of the [[Cultural Revolution]]. After the Cultural Revolution ended, she began studying history at [[Guizhou University]]. After graduating, she was sent to work for the provincial party school in Guizhou as a lecturer. She later became a human resources manager there. In 1998, she became vice president of the Guizhou party school. In 1999 she became Vice Chair of the Guizhou Social Sciences Academic Association.

In December 2001, Shen became deputy party chief of [[Qiannan Buyei and Miao Autonomous Prefecture]], then deputy party chief and head commissioner (mayor) of [[Tongren]].<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2012-02-25|url=http://gzsb.gog.com.cn/system/2003/01/30/000330814.shtml|title=杨玉学任铜仁地委书记 谌贻琴任铜仁行署专员|publisher=金黔在线|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518082436/http://gzsb.gog.com.cn/system/2003/01/30/000330814.shtml|archivedate=2015-05-18|df=}}</ref> In April 2007, Shen became a member of the provincial [[Party Standing Committee]] of Guizhou and head of the provincial party propaganda department.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2012-02-25|url=http://roll.sohu.com/20111108/n324908583.shtml|title=盘点32位女性省委常委从政之路|publisher=搜狐}}</ref>  In May 2012, she was named Executive Vice Governor of Guizhou.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2012-07-18|url=http://news.qbnews.cn/2012/0526/76189.html|title=十一届人大常委会二十八次会议闭幕 谌贻琴当选副省长|publisher=贵网|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130424162735/http://news.qbnews.cn/2012/0526/76189.html|archivedate=2013-04-24|df=}}</ref> In April 2015 she became Deputy Party Secretary of Guizhou and Secretary of Political and Legal Affairs Commission (''Zhengfawei'') of Guizhou.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://district.ce.cn/newarea/sddy/201504/23/t20150423_5195801.shtml|title=贵州省委副书记谌贻琴兼任政法委书记 秦如培不再担任|accessdate=2015-04-23|publisher=中国经济网}}</ref> At the time of her appointment to the deputy party chief position, she became the second sitting female ''zhuanzhi'' deputy party secretary in the country, and the only female provincial ''Zhengfawei'' chief in the country.<ref name=apple>{{cite news|title=谌贻琴履新贵州成中国首位女政法书记|url=https://news.powerapple.com/zhong-gang-tai/2015/4/24/2184993.html|publisher=Powerapple|date=April 24, 2015}}</ref> 

In September 2017, Shen was appointed as the acting Governor of Guizhou. Shen Yiqin is the first female Governor of Guizhou, the first Governor of Bai ethnic heritage, and the first Governor to have been born in province since 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.163.com/17/0906/19/CTM4U3880001875N.html|title=中国第三位女省长将诞生 还是当地第一位白族省长|accessdate=2017-09-06|publisher=政知圈 }}</ref>

Shen is an alternate member of the [[17th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|17th]] and the [[18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|18th]] Central Committees of the Communist Party of China, and a full member of the [[19th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|19th Central Committee]].

